declarations.description: Entire feature set for xtal-fetch, including multiple entity requests.
declarations.name: XtalFetchEntities

members.name: reqInit
members.description:
Object to use for second parameter of fetch method.  Can parse the value from the attribute if the attribute is in JSON format.
Supports JSON formatted attribute

members.name: cacheResults
members.description:
Indicates whether to pull the response from a previous identical fetch request from cache.
If set to true, cache is stored locally within the instance of the web component.
If set to 'global', cache is retained after web component goes out of scope.

members.name: reqInitRequired
members.description: Indicates that no fetch request should proceed until reqInit property / attribute is set.

members.name: debounceDuration
members.description: How long to pause between requests

members.name: errorResponse
members.description:
Error response as an object
⚡ Fires event error-response-changed

members.name: errorText
members.description:
Indicates the error text of the last request.
⚡ Fires event error-text-changed.

members.name: fetchInProgress
members.description:
Indicates Fetch is in progress
⚡ Fires event fetch-in-progress-changed

members.name: insertResults
members.description:
Indicate whether to set the innerHTML of the web component with the response from the server.  
Make sure the service is protected against XSS.

members.name: baseLinkId
members.description:
DOM ID  of link (preload) tag, typical in head element.  
Used to prov

members.name: fetch
members.description: Must be true for fetch to proceed

members.name: as
members.description: How to treat the response

members.name: href
members.description: URL (path) to fetch.

members.name: result
members.description:
⚡ Fires event result-changed
Result of fetch request
